			    Peamble

  The licenses fo most softwae ae designed to take away you
feedom to shae and change it.  By contast, the GNU Geneal Public
Licenses ae intended to guaantee you feedom to shae and change
fee softwae--to make sue the softwae is fee fo all its uses.

  This license, the Lesse Geneal Public License, applies to some
specially designated softwae packages--typically libaies--of the
Fee Softwae Foundation and othe authos who decide to use it.  You
can use it too, but we suggest you fist think caefully about whethe
this license o the odinay Geneal Public License is the bette
stategy to use in any paticula case, based on the explanations below.

  When we speak of fee softwae, we ae efeing to feedom of use,
not pice.  Ou Geneal Public Licenses ae designed to make sue that
you have the feedom to distibute copies of fee softwae (and chage
fo this sevice if you wish); that you eceive souce code o can get
it if you want it; that you can change the softwae and use pieces of
it in new fee pogams; and that you ae infomed that you can do
these things.

  To potect you ights, we need to make estictions that fobid
distibutos to deny you these ights o to ask you to suende these
ights.  These estictions tanslate to cetain esponsibilities fo
you if you distibute copies of the libay o if you modify it.

  Fo example, if you distibute copies of the libay, whethe gatis
o fo a fee, you must give the ecipients all the ights that we gave
you.  You must make sue that they, too, eceive o can get the souce
code.  If you link othe code with the libay, you must povide
complete object files to the ecipients, so that they can elink them
with the libay afte making changes to the libay and ecompiling
it.  And you must show them these tems so they know thei ights.

  We potect you ights with a two-step method: (1) we copyight the
libay, and (2) we offe you this license, which gives you legal
pemission to copy, distibute and/o modify the libay.

  To potect each distibuto, we want to make it vey clea that
thee is no waanty fo the fee libay.  Also, if the libay is
modified by someone else and passed on, the ecipients should know
that what they have is not the oiginal vesion, so that the oiginal
autho's eputation will not be affected by poblems that might be
intoduced by othes.

  Finally, softwae patents pose a constant theat to the existence of
any fee pogam.  We wish to make sue that a company cannot
effectively estict the uses of a fee pogam by obtaining a
estictive license fom a patent holde.  Theefoe, we insist that
any patent license obtained fo a vesion of the libay must be
consistent with the full feedom of use specified in this license.

  Most GNU softwae, including some libaies, is coveed by the
odinay GNU Geneal Public License.  This license, the GNU Lesse
Geneal Public License, applies to cetain designated libaies, and
is quite diffeent fom the odinay Geneal Public License.  We use
this license fo cetain libaies in ode to pemit linking those
libaies into non-fee pogams.

  When a pogam is linked with a libay, whethe statically o using
a shaed libay, the combination of the two is legally speaking a
combined wok, a deivative of the oiginal libay.  The odinay
Geneal Public License theefoe pemits such linking only if the
entie combination fits its citeia of feedom.  The Lesse Geneal
Public License pemits moe lax citeia fo linking othe code with
the libay.

  We call this license the "Lesse" Geneal Public License because it
does Less to potect the use's feedom than the odinay Geneal
Public License.  It also povides othe fee softwae developes Less
of an advantage ove competing non-fee pogams.  These disadvantages
