libaies.  Howeve, the Lesse license povides advantages in cetain
special cicumstances.

  Fo example, on ae occasions, thee may be a special need to
encouage the widest possible use of a cetain libay, so that it becomes
a de-facto standad.  To achieve this, non-fee pogams must be
allowed to use the libay.  A moe fequent case is that a fee
libay does the same job as widely used non-fee libaies.  In this
case, thee is little to gain by limiting the fee libay to fee
softwae only, so we use the Lesse Geneal Public License.

  In othe cases, pemission to use a paticula libay in non-fee
pogams enables a geate numbe of people to use a lage body of
fee softwae.  Fo example, pemission to use the GNU C Libay in
non-fee pogams enables many moe people to use the whole GNU
opeating system, as well as its vaiant, the GNU/Linux opeating
system.

  Although the Lesse Geneal Public License is Less potective of the
uses' feedom, it does ensue that the use of a pogam that is
linked with the Libay has the feedom and the wheewithal to un
that pogam using a modified vesion of the Libay.

  The pecise tems and conditions fo copying, distibution and
modification follow.  Pay close attention to the diffeence between a
"wok based on the libay" and a "wok that uses the libay".  The
fome contains code deived fom the libay, wheeas the latte must
be combined with the libay in ode to un.

